      "writtenOn": "2018-03-27T23:29:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Rack\u0027s FK is currently \"on delete set null\" (see below), but I think you\u0027re right it should cascade here and restrict below.\n\nAssuming KVM K and Rack R exist in the config and reference one another, the deletion cases are:\n1. Both are deleted from config. Server should delete R and cascade the deletion to K.\n2. K is deleted and the R-\u003eK reference is removed from the config. Server should update R to set its KVM to NULL, which removes the FK so K can be deleted. Server should delete K.\n3. K is not deleted and the R-\u003eK reference is removed from the config. Server should update R to set its KVM to NULL.\n4. K is deleted and the R-\u003eK reference is not removed from the config. Server should reject this as invalid (R references unknown KVM K).\n5. R is deleted and K is not deleted. Server should reject this as invalid (K references unknown rack R).",
      "parentUuid": "b7e7bfaa_02c06cd0",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 32,
        "startChar": 55,
        "endLine": 32,
        "endChar": 63
      },
